Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "situacija" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted by a star (*) and translations in parentheses:

1. Ova *situacija* postaje sve teža. (This *situation* is becoming increasingly difficult.)
2. Ne mogu da verujem u koju *situaciju* si upao. (I can't believe the *situation* you've gotten yourself into.)
3. U takvim *situacijama* ne treba paničiti. (In such *situations*, there's no need to panic.)
4. Nisam siguran kako bih se snašao u toj *situaciji*. (I'm not sure how I would cope in that *situation*.)
5. Kakva je *situacija* tamo? (What's the *situation* like over there?)
6. Da li imate neki savet za ovakve *situacije*? (Do you have any advice for these kinds of *situations*?)
7. U ovoj *situaciji*, moramo biti oprezni. (In this *situation*, we need to be careful.)
8. Moramo brzo reagovati na ovu *situaciju*. (We need to react quickly to this *situation*.)
9. Sve *situacije* su različite i zahtevaju drugačiji pristup. (All *situations* are different and require a different approach.)
10. Kako bi ste se ponašali u ovakvoj *situaciji*? (How would you behave in such a *situation*?)

Note: Please keep in mind that Serbian is a highly inflected language, so the word "situacija" can appear in various different forms depending on its grammatical role in the sentence. In these examples, I have provided a variety of different forms of the word to demonstrate its flexibility in different contexts.